node.title: Bumpy Ride
node.description: My wife and I hiked the Raven Cliff Falls trail in North GA this past weekend. I had not been before and was amazed with all the photo opportunities. This shot was taken pretty early in our hike before the lighting became too harsh. I certainly want to go back now--hopefully on a more overcast day.

node.title: Turkey in the Straw (Clover)
node.description: A turkey wades through fields of clover on a Spring afternoon in the Mountain Longleaf National Wildlife Refuge.

node.title: McClellan Icon B&W
node.description: Took this shot and several others on the main quad at McClellan last weekend.  As soon as I was done shooting this I felt a stinging sensation on my ankle, looked down, and found my foot halfway into a fire ant mound.  Ouch!

node.title: Weathered
node.description: Pinewood Chapel at Fort McClellan in Anniston, AL

node.title: Impressions of Spring
node.description: Vertical pan of spring wildflowers and woods in the Longleaf National Wildlife Refuge.  Please view on black.

node.title: What Used to Be
node.description: I was commissioned by a friend to take several shots of the old Anniston City Land Co. Building before it was torn down.  This was not a project I would ever chose, but one I ended up enjoying.   It's unfortunate that the building was not able to be restored, but t it was really in terrible shape.  You just don't see such detail in costrcution like this anymore.

node.title: Lower Bains
node.description: Another view of the lower falls at Bains Gap from last weekend.

node.title: Surge
node.description: The lower falls at Bains Gap were really flowing this past weekend.  The falls here are rarely more than a trickle, but this place is transformed after a series of heavy rains.  Hit "L" to view on black.
